      • hasSenderPD

        protected boolean hasSenderPD()
        Description copied from class: Frame
        Platform-dependent query indicating whether this frame has a sender. Should return true if it is possible to call sender() at all on this frame. (This is currently only needed for the debugging system, if a stack trace is attempted for a Java thread which has no Java frames, i.e., the signal thread; we have to know to stop traversal at the bottom frame.)
        Specified by:

      • getInterpreterFrameBCI

        public int getInterpreterFrameBCI()
        Description copied from class: Frame
        Byte code index. In the underlying frame, what is actually stored is a byte code pointer (BCP), which is converted to a BCI and back by the GC when methods are moved. In this system, interior pointers are not allowed, so we must make the access to the interpreter frame's BCI atomic with respect to GC. This may mean implementation with an underlying call through native code into the VM or a magic sequence in the compiler. (FIXME)
        Specified by:
        getInterpreterFrameBCI in class Frame
